\f[CR]HTMLSelectElement\f[R] interface is the numeric index of the first
selected \f[CR]<option>\f[R] element in a \f[CR]<select>\f[R] element,
if any, or \f[CR]âˆ’1\f[R] if no \f[CR]<option>\f[R] is selected.
Setting this property selects the option at that index and deselects all
other options, while setting it to \f[CR]\-1\f[R] deselects any
currently selected options.
